description:
Western Art 1600-1800
Thomson Learning | 1995 | ISBN: 1568472188 | English | 56 pages | PDF | 9.44 MB


A title from the ART AND ARTISTS series, with colour and black and white photographs and drawings to illustrate the dramatic changes that followed the Renaissance period, and how artists who had trained in Europe voyaged to the New World, taking their artistic influences with them
